race.description: Daryl Martin 17 Years Qtis 3YO Maiden Plate
race.comment: STORM MERCHANT (3) is a first-starter by Merchant Navy from the stakes-winner Miss Inbetween. Had caught the eye at the trials with two strong trial wins, making a mess of them in his most recent. Can make an immediate impact. STRIKE WEAPON (11) resumes a gelding. Was only sound on debut at Eagle Farm back in July when in the market but looks to have come on a treat during the break, scoring well in his lead-up trial here. Should make a bright return. OUR GIRL SCARLETT (5) was denied by the barest of margins second-up at Ipswich after again showing good early speed. Expect her to cross early from the wide draw and give another sight. SINFULL (8) debuts and keeps the blinkers on after a strong trial win here in readiness. Draws well and should be very competitive. HIT THE SWITCH (1) resumes for Matthew Hoysted. Was well supported when last sighted but left himself with too much to do. Two lead-up trials should have him forward enough to make his presence felt.
